21/11/2004
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- UNMIK chief Soren Jessen-Petersen met on Friday (19 November) with leaders of the political parties to discuss the establishment of new institutions in the province. He approved a government coalition agreement, which envisions the appointment of the Alliance for the Future of Kosovo's leader, Ramush Haradinaj, as prime minister. After the meeting, Haradinaj said the Kosovo institutions would be formed by the end of the week. Jessen-Petersen stressed the importance of setting them up as soon as possible, in order for talks on Kosovo's status to begin. (RTV, Tanjug, AFP, B92 - 19/11/04)
